<img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="Baldur&#039;s Gate 3 screenshot Credit Larian Studios" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/baldurs-gate-3-will-not-change-standards-director-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Responding to discourse regarding whether or not <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/baldurs-gate-iii"><em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em></a> should set a “ <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-should-not-set-the-standard-for-role-playing-games-warns-game-developers-3471538">new standard</a> ” for the role-playing genre, <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/larian-studios">Larian Studios</a> said that the industry moves too quickly for any standards to settle in.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE: <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-iii-early-access-classes-and-everything-you-need-to-know-2658339">Everything you need to know about &#39;Baldur&#39;s Gate 3&#39;</a></strong></li></ul><p> Swen Vincke, who is both the CEO of Larian Studios and the creative director of <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> , spoke in an interview on the most recent episode of the Friends Per Second <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yeLK8Wc-zPY" target="_blank" rel="noopener">podcast</a> (July 30).</p><p> “When I started out, <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/ubisoft">Ubisoft</a> launched <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/assassins-creed"><em>Assassin&#39;s Creed</em></a> , and everybody was saying, &#39;everything&#39;s going to be like <em>Assassin&#39;s Creed</em> , you&#39;re all doomed, no one&#39;s going to be able to make this game anymore,&#39;” recalled Vincke. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Baldur’s Gate 3 boss on Xbox Series S and “Redefining The RPG” I Friends Per Second Episode #26" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/yeLK8Wc-zPY?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> He stressed that <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> has benefitted from a large team but that there is “so much stuff” that developers could create rather than copying or emulating the upcoming fantasy role-playing game.</p><p> “When it comes to standards, standards change continuously, so I don&#39;t think that is something people should be worried about [with <em>Baldur&#39;s Gate 3</em> ],” continued the CEO. “Games like ours are very specific, it&#39;s what we wanted to make and what we specialize in so it&#39;s logical that we have a certain pedigree in creating it. Because we&#39;ve been building these games for 20 years already.”</p><p> Set up in 1996, Larian Studios has developed a sizeable number of games, including educational ones, but it is <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-developer-will-get-back-to-divinity-original-sin-after-a-break-3474609">most famous for the <em>Divinity</em> series</a> .</p><p> “I don&#39;t think there&#39;s such a thing as a game that says &#39;Oh this is the standard, and everyone has to hold themselves to it,&#39; because tomorrow somebody else will come up with something new and cool,” concluded Vincke. “Standards change so rapidly that there are no standards.”</p><p> In other gaming news, the <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/path-of-exile-2"><em>Path of Exile 2</em></a> team said that <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/path-of-exile-2-dev-says-blizzard-learned-hard-lessons-with-diablo-4-3475624">it feels “very bad”</a> for <a href="https://www.nme.com/brands/blizzard-entertainment">Blizzard Entertainment</a> following the poor response to <a href="https://www.nme.com/games/diablo-iv"><em>Diablo 4</em></a> &#39;s patch 1.1.1.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/gaming-news/baldurs-gate-3-dev-says-it-wont-elevate-the-standard-for-rpgs-because-something-cooler-will-come-along-3475653">&#39;Baldur&#39;s Gate 3&#39; dev says it won&#39;t elevate the “standard” for RPGs because something cooler will come along</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
